In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Place broccoli in a medium microwave-safe #bowl{} and cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. Drain any excess liquid and keep covered until ready to use in Step 5.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, @ground beef{10%ounce}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until beef is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

> Swap in tofu for beef (no need to break tofu up into pieces!).

While beef cooks, in a small #bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and as much @Sriracha{1%tsp} as you like. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Remove pan with beef mixture from heat; stir in @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, add a splash of water.

Transfer saucy beef to bowl with broccoli; toss until everything is fully coated.

> TIP: If rice is still cooking, cover turkey and broccoli mixture to keep warm until ready to serve.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with beef and broccoli. Drizzle with Sriracha mayo and garnish with scallion greens. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.